{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a module-handoff correctness check (changed-file discovery -> analysis target set). Unit tests on filtering logic alone can miss wiring bugs between PR-diff input and scanner selection. I considered System, but rejected it because the behavior text does not require validating real GitHub API response contracts or an external round-trip side effect; it only states selection correctness.","test_description":"Run the lint step in a local integration harness with a fixture PR change-set containing changed and unchanged files, then assert the analyzer is invoked only for changed paths and never for unchanged ones.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"Success is defined at an external boundary: the PR comment that is actually posted. Per the round-trip effect rule, this requires proving externally visible side effects via real write/readback. Mocks can hide serialization/formatting/API-shape issues.","test_description":"Execute the action against a real test PR, post findings, then read back the created PR comment via GitHub API and verify sections are grouped as error/warning/info with correct membership.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"This depends on real CI runtime behavior and timeout constraints in GitHub Actions. Unit/integration benchmarks can miss runner/environment overhead. I considered Integration, but rejected it because the behavior text explicitly anchors correctness to Actions timeout, which is an external system condition.","test_description":"Trigger the GitHub Action on a PR fixture with ~200 changed files and assert end-to-end job completion before 10 minutes using actual Actions run timing/status.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly involves real process-failure handling (crash) plus externally visible posting of results. This matches System (real subprocess/error-path contract and external side-effect verification). Integration-only exception simulation risks false confidence.","test_description":"Run the pipeline with one intentionally malformed file that causes the real linter subprocess to crash, verify the step continues analyzing subsequent files, and confirm a PR comment is posted containing findings from remaining files plus crash reporting.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Deduplication risk is mainly at module boundaries where outputs from multiple rules are merged before rendering. Unit tests for the dedupe function may miss schema/normalization mismatches between rule producers and aggregator. I considered System, but rejected it because behavior text does not require external contract validation or external round-trip visibility; I considered Agentic/Workflow and rejected both because no AI/LLM dependency is described.","test_description":"Wire multiple real rule modules in an integration test so they emit overlapping findings for the same file/line, run aggregation/output formatting, and assert only one canonical finding is emitted for that location.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.38,"Integration":0.57,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
